cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.SE, cs.FL

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the adaptation of sup-interpretations to a fragment of object-oriented programs, which involves logical reasoning.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper deals with the control of resources in programs, which is a core concern of programming languages.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper deals with the size of values computed by programs, which is related to data structures and algorithms.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper deals with the control of resources in programs, which is a key aspect of software engineering.
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is relevant as the paper deals with the characterization of functions computable in a certain complexity class, which is related to formal languages and automata theory.
